{
  "texts": [
    "In particular, the eROSITA Final Equatorial Depth Survey (eFEDS; Brunner et al. 2022), designed to provide uniform exposure over a sufficiently large field (140 deg 2) about 50% deeper than what is expected for eRASS at the end of the 4 yr all-sky survey programme, has shown that large samples of X-ray sources of different classes can be detected, identified, and characterised making use of the synergy with existing A34, page 2 of 38 Merloni, A., et al.",
    ": A&A, 682, A34 (2024) multi-wavelength surveys (see, e.g.",
    "Ghirardini et al. 2021; Liu et al.",
    "2022a,b; Salvato et al. 2022; Klein et al.",
    "2022; Schneider et al. 2022; Bulbul et al."
  ]
}